  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook the rice following packet instructions. Finely slice the red chilli and the spring onion, separating the onion whites and greens."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To a blender, add ½ the spinach, the coriander, coconut milk, soy sauce, stock cube, agave (if using) and vegan fish sauce (if using). Blitz until smooth."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a glug of vegetable oil in a large pan set over a low heat. Add the curry paste and spring onion whites and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 mins until fragrant. Add the water, remaining spinach and the blended green sauce to the pan. Leave to gently come to a simmer. Season with lime juice to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice the baby corn into bite-sized chunks. Heat a drizzle of vegetable oil in a new large pan set over a high heat. Add the baby corn with a pinch of salt and fry for 2 mins, then add the mangetout and cook for another 3 mins until softened and starting to brown."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove the veg from the pan then crumble in the tofu. Add another splash of vegetable oil and cook the tofu over a high heat for 3-4 mins, then add the soy sauce and sesame seeds and cook for another 3 mins until really crisped up."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, divide the rice between bowls, pour over the green sauce and top with the charred veggies and crispy tofu. Finish with the sliced chilli, spring onion greens and a wedge of lime, if you like."
    }
  ],
